title: For Sale:  Exc. Cond. Remington 870 Wingmaster 12 GA
postcontent:
Hello, and thanks for looking! Well, after debating for several years, I have decided to part with one of my prized possessions; this was the first shotgun I ever owned, having bought it from my next-door-neighbor way back in 1980; he had only bought it the year before, and didn't want to hunt anymore due to sudden health issues, so he sold it to me. Sometime in the mid- to late 90's, I bought a 26' light contour RemChoke w/ventilated rib barrel, and that's the only barrel this gun comes with; I see from the various websites out there that the same barrel, with 3 choke tubes, sells for about $209 today. There are 3 factory Remington choke tubes included - Imp. Cylinder, Modified, and Full - Steel or Lead. I also will include a Mossberg Skeet tube that was made for the 870, along with the wrench needed to install them. In addition, the stock and forend have been expertly refinished by my late Father, and they look fantastic. There are a couple of light, hairline scratches on the receiver (which is chambered only for 2 3/4" shells, so please make a note of this), but overall, the finish is in excellent condition; the gun would rate at least 95%+, according to the Blue Book grading guidelines. The  only thing I would mention as a potential negative would be the fact that the bluing has worn off of most of the magazine tube, which would be rather common in this model gun, especially for one of this age.

Considering the price of the barrel alone, this gun is an excellent value - I'll entertain reasonable offers, but if you're not in the range of my target price, I'll have to keep it. If you're looking for a great waterfowling gun, your search is over!

Additional pictures available upon request; thanks again for looking!
